---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="The Matrix" description="An interactive bio detailing Sandeep Singh's intellectual layout connecting systems engineering to macroeconomic cycles, polity, and global affairs.">
  <div class="space-y-12">
    
    <!-- Page Header -->
    <div class="space-y-4 border-b border-white/5 pb-8">
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold font-heading text-white">
        The <span class="text-gradient-gold">Matrix</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-silver/70 max-w-3xl leading-relaxed">
        An interactive cognitive ledger mapping out my multidisciplinary worldview, connecting first-principles computer science to the macro-mechanics of governance, geopolitics, and monetary systems.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Core Synthesis Panel -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
      
      <!-- Profile Coordinates Card -->
      <div class="glassmorphism rounded-xl p-6 border border-white/5 space-y-6 lg:col-span-1">
        <div class="flex items-center space-x-4">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-gradient-to-tr from-sovereign to-cyber flex items-center justify-center font-heading font-extrabold text-dark-950 text-xl">
            SS
          </div>
          <div>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-heading font-bold text-white leading-none">Sandeep Singh</h2>
            <span class="text-xs font-mono text-sovereign">[COGNITIVE_NODE]</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-4 text-xs font-mono">
          <div class="border-t border-white/5 pt-4">
            <span class="text-silver/40 block mb-1">QUALIFICATION</span>
            <span class="text-white font-semibold">B.E. Computer Engineering</span>
            <span class="text-silver/60 block">Thapar Institute of Eng. & Tech</span>
          </div>
          <div class="border-t border-white/5 pt-4">
            <span class="text-silver/40 block mb-1">EXPERIENCE</span>
            <span class="text-white font-semibold">Graduate Engineering Trainee</span>
            <span class="text-cyber font-semibold">Addverb Technologies</span>
            <span class="text-silver/60 block">WMS API Development & Bug Resolution</span>
          </div>
          <div class="border-t border-white/5 pt-4">
            <span class="text-silver/40 block mb-1">CORE_SKILLS</span>
            <span class="text-white block">Java, Spring Boot, Python, SQL, RabbitMQ</span>
          </div>
          <div class="border-t border-white/5 pt-4">
            <span class="text-silver/40 block mb-1">LOCALE</span>
            <span class="text-white">Batala, Punjab, India</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Cognitive Map (Interactive Bio Columns) -->
      <div class="lg:col-span-2 space-y-6">
        
        <!-- Manifesto Card -->
        <div class="glassmorphism rounded-xl p-6 border border-white/5 space-y-4">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-bold text-white">The Systems Synthesis Manifesto</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-silver/70 leading-relaxed">
            In standard software engineering, we isolate subsystems to handle failures. In government affairs, constitutions act as the original isolated runtime containers, establishing separation of powers so that single-node corruption doesn't trigger systemic state corruption. 
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-silver/70 leading-relaxed">
            I do not view code, polity, or inflation as separate subjects. They are structural models of how energy, resources, and instructions are distributed across networks. Software systems are simply high-velocity simulations of governance.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- The Matrix Nodes Grid -->
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          
          <!-- Node 0: Tech -->
          <div class="interactive-card border-l-2 border-l-cyber">
            <h4 class="font-heading font-bold text-white text-base">Node_0: Backend Architecture</h4>
            <p class="text-xs text-silver/60 leading-relaxed pt-2">
              Focuses on deterministic computations, Spring Boot dependency injections, concurrent API loops, and transactional database normalizations. High-precision backend execution.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Node 1: Polity -->
          <div class="interactive-card border-l-2 border-l-sovereign">
            <h4 class="font-heading font-bold text-white text-base">Node_1: Indian Polity & Law</h4>
            <p class="text-xs text-silver/60 leading-relaxed pt-2">
              Auditing regulatory institutions, cabinet powers, parliamentary defection (10th Schedule), and the jurisdictional bounds of Article 12 enforcing fundamental rights.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Node 2: Economics -->
          <div class="interactive-card border-l-2 border-l-red-500">
            <h4 class="font-heading font-bold text-white text-base">Node_2: Macroeconomics</h4>
            <p class="text-xs text-silver/60 leading-relaxed pt-2">
              Investigating fiat monetary inflation, deficit public-works financing (Henry Hazlitt's Chapter 22), the Cantillon wealth redistribution mechanism, and global exchange rates.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Node 3: Geopolitics -->
          <div class="interactive-card border-l-2 border-l-amber-500">
            <h4 class="font-heading font-bold text-white text-base">Node_3: Geopolitical Pivots</h4>
            <p class="text-xs text-silver/60 leading-relaxed pt-2">
              Analyzing spatial geographic rivalries, energy transit pipes, territorial Caucasus realignments (Russia-Turkey-Iran), and trade corridor supply lines.
            </p>
          </div>

        </div>

      </div>

    </div>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>
